
          The Shadow of the Third Moon - Demo version


This is first Demo-Version of a new fanatastic ActionFlightSimulator.
TSOT3rdM uses a brandnew voxelengine technics, which brings a never
seen before realism flight simulation to your AMIGA. Forget ugly
vector-base flightsimulations.
The Game will be available on August 1997, direct from our local
Amiga-Dealer or from:

 Titan Computer
 Mahndorfer Heerstr. 80 A
 D-28307 Bremen / Germany
 Tel/Fax.: +49/(0)421/48 16 20

 E-Mail: TitanHB@vossnet.de
 Web: Http://www.vossnet.de/titanhb/

Suggested retail price is DM 89.-, £35, $50.

.....................................................................


System requirements:

- Amiga O.S. v39 or newer
- RAM: min. 4MB Fast RAM
            8MB for enhanced GFX set or SVGA chunky graphics
- 256 colors hires graphics with complete R.T.G. system
- CDROM 2x or faster
- CPU 68030/25Mhz or faster
- ~25MB HD free space
- Multiscan monitor for 640x480 flicker-free graphics
- HiFi system ;-)

- Racommended:

  - 68030/50Mhz or faster
  - 8MB Fast RAM 60ns
  - SVGA
  - CDROM 4x (600KB/s)

Performance (High detail setting - 320x240x256 - pixel 1x1):

 ~5.5 fps  - 68030/25 (A4000/Ec030 - AGA - C2P 68030)
 ~11 fps   - 68030/50 (A1200/Bliz50 or A4000/A3640 - AGA -
             C2P 68030+ and nAo_c2p)
 ~12 fps   - 68040/25 (A4000/A3640 - CyberGraphX)
 25-50 fps - 68060/50 (A4000/Cy060 - CyberGraphX or C2P 68060)



Supported graphic modes :

- AGA (320x240x256, 640x480x256), using display database
  Chunky to planar conversion algorithms optimized for 68030, 68030+,
  68040 and 68060.

- CyberGraphX support (Chunky8, CGFX v2.x)

- Generic RTG is also available to support any other graphics card.
  (PicassoXX, Retina, Merlin, etc...)

Music:

- 11 High quality CDDA audio tracks - 16bit 44.1 Khz
  (49 minutes)

- SFX - 8bit stereo

Media:

- Full-sized CDRom (680MB).

Graphics:

- Real time landscape rendering performed by 3dTIS algorithms
  (© Black Blade software design - Italy 1995-97)

- Fog and global haze effect.

- Semi-transparent smoke.

- Raytraced bitmap objects are printed using the VecBitmap method (©
  Black Blade software design - Italia 1995-97) to add good realism to
  the speed of fixed bitmap objects.

- Ray-traced static graphics.

- Graphic objects VecBitmap (© Black Blade software design - Italy
  1995-97):

  normal (4MB fast RAM)
  extended (8MB fast RAM)

- Elevation-mapped landscapes (15km x 15km virtual size)

- Particle explosions

- Photorealistic cloudy sky

Controls:

- Digital joystick + keyboard

- Mouse + keyboard

Gameplay:

- Missions linked, sequential storyline

- Fun and amazingly realistic

- Dynamic adventure storyline

- Improved enemy AI

Notes:

VGA cards have a 18bit palette in 256 colours modes, since AGA has
24bit one. So the quality of graphics is quite lower on gfx card
compared to the AGA. Anyway VGA can give you a higher framerate.


